Title: What biting your cheek REALLY means
Creator: FootDocDana
Transcript: [Music] This is called morsicatio buckarum. Basically a fancy name for when you unconsciously chew the inside of your cheek. It could sometimes be caused by misaligned teeth malusion which could lead to accidental biting. But if the biting is excessive, this could be a sign of a mental health disorder. a subset of body focused repetitive behaviors. A group of disorders where individuals engage in actions like biting, picking, pulling in response to emotional distress or anxiety or even boredom. For many people, these habits provide a temporary sense of relief and distraction. But over time, they can cause physical harm such as scars or soarses in the mouth and even permanent damage to the tissue inside the cheek.
